cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formalising the behaviour of concurrent processes and manipulating global types.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses typing of multiparty sessions and subtyping relations.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper deals with communication between multiple participants.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses lock-freedom, which is an important property in concurrent programming.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with manipulating global types and the behaviour of concurrent processes.
